{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"chatcmpl-tool-871b2d96a1f3b79a","type":"tool_result","content":"850\tCF-Net achieves 80% No-AH recall and 67% AH recall.</figcaption>\n851\t</figure>\n852\t</section>\n853\t<section id=\"S4.SS4\" class=\"ltx_subsection\">\n854\t<h3 class=\"ltx_title ltx_title_subsection\">\n855\t<span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_tag_subsection\"><span id=\"S4.SS4.4.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\">IV-D</span> </span><span id=\"S4.SS4.5.2\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_italic\">Ablation Study</span>\n856\t</h3>\n857\t\n858\t<div id=\"S4.SS4.p1\" class=\"ltx_para\">\n859\t<p id=\"S4.SS4.p1.1\" class=\"ltx_p\"><a href=\"#S4.T2\" title=\"In IV-D Ablation Study ‣ IV Experiments ‣ CF-Net: Conflict Fusion with Speaker Normalisation and Certainty Weighting for Ambivalence/Hesitancy Recognition\" class=\"ltx_ref\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag\">Table</span> <span class=\"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag\">II</span></a> isolates the contribution of each component.\n860\tAll ablations use the CF-Net architecture as the base.</p>\n861\t</div>\n862\t<figure id=\"S4.T2\" class=\"ltx_table\">\n863\t<figcaption class=\"ltx_caption\"><span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_tag_table\">TABLE II: </span>Incremental ablation on BAH validation set, adding one component\n864\tat a time from the top down. Unimodal baselines use a BiLSTM temporal\n865\tencoder; the switch to BiGRU is its own ablation step.\n866\tMacro F1<math id=\"S4.T2.2.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"\\uparrow\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo stretchy=\"false\">↑</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\uparrow</annotation></semantics></math>; best in bold.</figcaption>\n867\t<table id=\"S4.T2.15\" class=\"ltx_tabular ltx_centering ltx_guessed_headers ltx_align_middle\">\n868\t<thead class=\"ltx_thead\">\n869\t<tr id=\"S4.T2.3.1\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n870\t<th id=\"S4.T2.3.1.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_th ltx_th_column ltx_border_tt\">Configuration</th>\n871\t<th id=\"S4.T2.3.1.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center ltx_th ltx_th_column ltx_border_tt\">Val Macro F1<math id=\"S4.T2.3.1.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"\\uparrow\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo stretchy=\"false\">↑</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\uparrow</annotation></semantics></math>\n872\t</th>\n873\t</tr>\n874\t</thead>\n875\t<tbody class=\"ltx_tbody\">\n876\t<tr id=\"S4.T2.4.2\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n877\t<td id=\"S4.T2.4.2.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">Text only (DistilBERT <math id=\"S4.T2.4.2.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"+\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo>+</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">+</annotation></semantics></math> classifier)</td>\n878\t<td id=\"S4.T2.4.2.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\">0.6505</td>\n879\t</tr>\n880\t<tr id=\"S4.T2.5.3\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n881\t<td id=\"S4.T2.5.3.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left\">Audio only (HuBERT <math id=\"S4.T2.5.3.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"+\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo>+</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">+</annotation></semantics></math> BiLSTM)</td>\n882\t<td id=\"S4.T2.5.3.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center\">0.4672</td>\n883\t</tr>\n884\t<tr id=\"S4.T2.6.4\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n885\t<td id=\"S4.T2.6.4.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left\">Visual only (SigLIP2 <math id=\"S4.T2.6.4.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"+\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo>+</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">+</annotation></semantics></math> BiLSTM)</td>\n886\t<td id=\"S4.T2.6.4.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center\">0.5888</td>\n887\t</tr>\n888\t<tr id=\"S4.T2.15.14.1\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n889\t<td id=\"S4.T2.15.14.1.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left\">All modalities, mean fusion</td>\n890\t<td id=\"S4.T2.15.14.1.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center\">0.6428</td>\n891\t</tr>\n892\t<tr id=\"S4.T2.15.15.2\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n893\t<td id=\"S4.T2.15.15.2.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left\">All modalities, ConflictFusion (no aux head)</td>\n894\t<td id=\"S4.T2.15.15.2.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center\">0.6612</td>\n895\t</tr>\n896\t<tr id=\"S4.T2.7.5\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n897\t<td id=\"S4.T2.7.5.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left\">\n898\t<math id=\"S4.T2.7.5.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"+\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo>+</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">+</annotation></semantics></math> Auxiliary certainty head</td>\n899\t<td id=\"S4.T2.7.5.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center\">0.6722</td>\n900\t</tr>\n901\t<tr id=\"S4.T2.10.8\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n902\t<td id=\"S4.T2.10.8.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left\">\n903\t<math id=\"S4.T2.8.6.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"+\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo>+</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">+</annotation></semantics></math> Focal loss <math id=\"S4.T2.9.7.2.m2\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"+\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo>+</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">+</annotation></semantics></math> Manifold mixup (<math id=\"S4.T2.10.8.3.m3\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"\\alpha=0.2\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mrow><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0.2</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\alpha=0.2</annotation></semantics></math>)</td>\n904\t<td id=\"S4.T2.10.8.4\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center\">0.6870</td>\n905\t</tr>\n906\t<tr id=\"S4.T2.12.10\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n907\t<td id=\"S4.T2.12.10.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left\">\n908\t<math id=\"S4.T2.11.9.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"+\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo>+</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">+</annotation></semantics></math> Modality dropout (<math id=\"S4.T2.12.10.2.m2\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"p=0.15\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0.15</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p=0.15</annotation></semantics></math>)</td>\n909\t<td id=\"S4.T2.12.10.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center\">0.6984</td>\n910\t</tr>\n911\t<tr id=\"S4.T2.13.11\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n912\t<td id=\"S4.T2.13.11.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left\">\n913\t<math id=\"S4.T2.13.11.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"+\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo>+</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">+</annotation></semantics></math> Speaker normalisation</td>\n914\t<td id=\"S4.T2.13.11.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center\">0.7110</td>\n915\t</tr>\n916\t<tr id=\"S4.T2.14.12\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n917\t<td id=\"S4.T2.14.12.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left\">\n918\t<math id=\"S4.T2.14.12.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"+\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo>+</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">+</annotation></semantics></math> BiGRU encoder</td>\n919\t<td id=\"S4.T2.14.12.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center\">0.7136</td>\n920\t</tr>\n921\t<tr id=\"S4.T2.15.13\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n922\t<td id=\"S4.T2.15.13.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_bb\">\n923\t<math id=\"S4.T2.15.13.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"+\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo>+</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">+</annotation></semantics></math> Certainty-weighted focal loss</td>\n924\t<td id=\"S4.T2.15.13.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center ltx_border_bb\"><span id=\"S4.T2.15.13.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_bold\">0.7155</span></td>\n925\t</tr>\n926\t</tbody>\n927\t</table>\n928\t</figure>\n929\t</section>\n930\t<section id=\"S4.SS5\" class=\"ltx_subsection\">\n931\t<h3 class=\"ltx_title ltx_title_subsection\">\n932\t<span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_tag_subsection\"><span id=\"S4.SS5.4.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\">IV-E</span> </span><span id=\"S4.SS5.5.2\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_italic\">Comparison with Prior Work</span>\n933\t</h3>\n934\t\n935\t<div id=\"S4.SS5.p1\" class=\"ltx_para\">\n936\t<p id=\"S4.SS5.p1.1\" class=\"ltx_p\"><a href=\"#S4.T3\" title=\"In IV-E Comparison with Prior Work ‣ IV Experiments ‣ CF-Net: Conflict Fusion with Speaker Normalisation and Certainty Weighting for Ambivalence/Hesitancy Recognition\" class=\"ltx_ref\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag\">Table</span> <span class=\"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag\">III</span></a> compares CF-Net against published methods on both the\n937\tofficial BAH validation split and the private challenge test set.\n938\tPrior methods are drawn from the 10<sup id=\"S4.SS5.p1.1.1\" class=\"ltx_sup\">th</sup> ABAW challenge\n939\t(CVPR 2026) <cite class=\"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite\">[<a href=\"#bib.bib12\" title=\"From affect to complex behavior: advancing multimodal human-centered ai at the 10th abaw workshop &amp; competition\" class=\"ltx_ref\">8</a>]</cite>; CF-Net was submitted to the\n940\t11<sup id=\"S4.SS5.p1.1.2\" class=\"ltx_sup\">th</sup> ABAW challenge (ECCV 2026).</p>\n941\t</div>\n942\t<figure id=\"S4.T3\" class=\"ltx_table\">\n943\t<figcaption class=\"ltx_caption\"><span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_tag_table\">TABLE III: </span>Comparison on the BAH validation and private test sets.\n944\t<math id=\"S4.T3.3.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"\\uparrow\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo stretchy=\"false\">↑</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\uparrow</annotation></semantics></math>: higher is better.\n945\t<span id=\"S4.T3.14.1\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_bold\">—</span>: not reported.\n946\t<sup id=\"S4.T3.15.2\" class=\"ltx_sup\">‡</sup>: 10th ABAW test (161 videos); CF-Net on 11th ABAW test (152 videos).</figcaption>\n947\t<table id=\"S4.T3.11\" class=\"ltx_tabular ltx_centering ltx_align_middle\">\n948\t<tbody class=\"ltx_tbody\">\n949\t<tr id=\"S4.T3.6.2\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n950\t<td id=\"S4.T3.6.2.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_tt\"><span id=\"S4.T3.6.2.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">Method</span></td>\n951\t<td id=\"S4.T3.5.1.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_tt\">\n952\t<span id=\"S4.T3.5.1.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">Val F1</span><math id=\"S4.T3.5.1.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"\\uparrow\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo mathsize=\"0.800em\" stretchy=\"false\">↑</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\uparrow</annotation></semantics></math>\n953\t</td>\n954\t<td id=\"S4.T3.6.2.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center ltx_border_tt\">\n955\t<span id=\"S4.T3.6.2.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">Test F1</span><math id=\"S4.T3.6.2.2.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"\\uparrow\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo mathsize=\"0.800em\" stretchy=\"false\">↑</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\uparrow</annotation></semantics></math>\n956\t</td>\n957\t</tr>\n958\t<tr id=\"S4.T3.11.8.1\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n959\t<td id=\"S4.T3.11.8.1.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">\n960\t<span id=\"S4.T3.11.8.1.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">Organiser baseline </span><cite class=\"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite\"><span id=\"S4.T3.11.8.1.1.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">[</span><a href=\"#bib.bib11\" title=\"BAH dataset for ambivalence/hesitancy recognition in videos for digital behavioural change\" class=\"ltx_ref\">5</a><span id=\"S4.T3.11.8.1.1.3.2\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">]</span></cite>\n961\t</td>\n962\t<td id=\"S4.T3.11.8.1.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S4.T3.11.8.1.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">–</span></td>\n963\t<td id=\"S4.T3.11.8.1.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S4.T3.11.8.1.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">0.2827</span></td>\n964\t</tr>\n965\t<tr id=\"S4.T3.7.3\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n966\t<td id=\"S4.T3.7.3.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">\n967\t<span id=\"S4.T3.7.3.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">Team Time Visao </span><cite class=\"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite\"><span id=\"S4.T3.7.3.2.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">[</span><a href=\"#bib.bib8\" title=\"Solution for 10th competition on ambivalence/hesitancy (ah) video recognition challenge using divergence-based multimodal fusion\" class=\"ltx_ref\">18</a><span id=\"S4.T3.7.3.2.3.2\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">]</span></cite>\n968\t</td>\n969\t<td id=\"S4.T3.7.3.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S4.T3.7.3.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">0.652</span></td>\n970\t<td id=\"S4.T3.7.3.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\"><math id=\"S4.T3.7.3.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"0.536^{\\ddagger}\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><msup><mn mathsize=\"0.800em\">0.536</mn><mo mathsize=\"0.800em\">‡</mo></msup><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">0.536^{\\ddagger}</annotation></semantics></math></td>\n971\t</tr>\n972\t<tr id=\"S4.T3.8.4\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n973\t<td id=\"S4.T3.8.4.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left\">\n974\t<span id=\"S4.T3.8.4.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">Team Lenovo PCIE </span><cite class=\"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite\"><span id=\"S4.T3.8.4.2.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">[</span><a href=\"#bib.bib6\" title=\"Nuanced emotion recognition based on a segment-based mllm framework leveraging qwen3-omni for ah detection\" class=\"ltx_ref\">19</a><span id=\"S4.T3.8.4.2.3.2\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">]</span></cite>\n975\t</td>\n976\t<td id=\"S4.T3.8.4.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center\"><span id=\"S4.T3.8.4.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_bold\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">–</span></td>\n977\t<td id=\"S4.T3.8.4.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center\"><math id=\"S4.T3.8.4.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"0.675^{\\ddagger}\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><msup><mn mathsize=\"0.800em\">0.675</mn><mo mathsize=\"0.800em\">‡</mo></msup><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">0.675^{\\ddagger}</annotation></semantics></math></td>\n978\t</tr>\n979\t<tr id=\"S4.T3.9.5\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n980\t<td id=\"S4.T3.9.5.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left\">\n981\t<span id=\"S4.T3.9.5.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">Team LEYA </span><cite class=\"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite\"><span id=\"S4.T3.9.5.2.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">[</span><a href=\"#bib.bib10\" title=\"Team leya in 10th abaw competition: multimodal ambivalence/hesitancy recognition approach\" class=\"ltx_ref\">14</a><span id=\"S4.T3.9.5.2.3.2\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">]</span></cite>\n982\t</td>\n983\t<td id=\"S4.T3.9.5.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center\"><span id=\"S4.T3.9.5.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_bold\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">0.830</span></td>\n984\t<td id=\"S4.T3.9.5.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center\"><math id=\"S4.T3.9.5.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"0.714^{\\ddagger}\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><msup><mn mathsize=\"0.800em\">0.714</mn><mo mathsize=\"0.800em\">‡</mo></msup><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">0.714^{\\ddagger}</annotation></semantics></math></td>\n985\t</tr>\n986\t<tr id=\"S4.T3.10.6\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n987\t<td id=\"S4.T3.10.6.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left\">\n988\t<span id=\"S4.T3.10.6.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">Team Fennec </span><cite class=\"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite\"><span id=\"S4.T3.10.6.2.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">[</span><a href=\"#bib.bib7\" title=\"Conflict-aware multimodal fusion for ambivalence and hesitancy recognition\" class=\"ltx_ref\">2</a><span id=\"S4.T3.10.6.2.3.2\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">]</span></cite>\n989\t</td>\n990\t<td id=\"S4.T3.10.6.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center\"><span id=\"S4.T3.10.6.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">0.746</span></td>\n991\t<td id=\"S4.T3.10.6.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center\"><math id=\"S4.T3.10.6.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"0.715^{\\ddagger}\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><msup><mn mathsize=\"0.800em\">0.715</mn><mo mathsize=\"0.800em\">‡</mo></msup><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">0.715^{\\ddagger}</annotation></semantics></math></td>\n992\t</tr>\n993\t<tr id=\"S4.T3.11.7\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n994\t<td id=\"S4.T3.11.7.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left\">\n995\t<span id=\"S4.T3.11.7.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">Team BROTHER </span><cite class=\"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite\"><span id=\"S4.T3.11.7.2.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">[</span><a href=\"#bib.bib9\" title=\"Brother: behavioral recognition optimized through heterogeneous ensemble regularization for ambivalence and hesitancy\" class=\"ltx_ref\">12</a><span id=\"S4.T3.11.7.2.3.2\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">]</span></cite>\n996\t</td>\n997\t<td id=\"S4.T3.11.7.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center\"><span id=\"S4.T3.11.7.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">0.736</span></td>\n998\t<td id=\"S4.T3.11.7.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center\"><math id=\"S4.T3.11.7.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"0.727^{\\ddagger}\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><msup><mn mathsize=\"0.800em\">0.727</mn><mo mathsize=\"0.800em\">‡</mo></msup><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">0.727^{\\ddagger}</annotation></semantics></math></td>\n999\t</tr>\n1000\t<tr id=\"S4.T3.11.9.2\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n1001\t<td id=\"S4.T3.11.9.2.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_bb ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S4.T3.11.9.2.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">CF-Net (ours)</span></td>\n1002\t<td id=\"S4.T3.11.9.2.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_bb ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S4.T3.11.9.2.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">0.716</span></td>\n1003\t<td id=\"S4.T3.11.9.2.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_nopad_r ltx_align_center ltx_border_bb ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S4.T3.11.9.2.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_bold\" style=\"font-size:80%;\">0.7364</span></td>\n1004\t</tr>\n1005\t</tbody>\n1006\t</table>\n1007\t</figure>\n1008\t<div id=\"S4.SS5.p2\" class=\"ltx_para\">\n1009\t<p id=\"S4.SS5.p2.2\" class=\"ltx_p\">On the validation set, CF-Net (0.716) outperforms the organiser baseline\n1010\tby <math id=\"S4.SS5.p2.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"+\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo>+</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">+</annotation></semantics></math>6.0 points; Team LEYA (0.854) leads through end-to-end fine-tuning\n1011\tbut shows severe overfitting (0.854 to 0.714 on the private test).\n1012\tOn the 10th ABAW private test, BROTHER achieves the best score (0.747)\n1013\tvia ensemble optimisation, followed by ConflictAwareAH (0.715) and\n1014\tLEYA (0.714).\n1015\tCF-Net achieves <span id=\"S4.SS5.p2.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_bold\">0.7364</span> on the 11th ABAW private test — a\n1016\tdifferent held-out set — which is between ConflictAwareAH and BROTHER,\n1017\tas a single non-ensemble frozen-backbone model.\n1018\tThe val-to-test improvement (<math id=\"S4.SS5.p2.2.m2\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"+\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo>+</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">+</annotation></semantics></math>0.021) confirms that per-speaker\n1019\tnormalisation and certainty-weighted focal loss generalise to unseen\n1020\tspeakers rather than memorising the validation set.</p>\n1021\t</div>\n1022\t</section>\n1023\t</section>\n1024\t<section id=\"S5\" class=\"ltx_section\">\n1025\t<h2 class=\"ltx_title ltx_title_section\">\n1026\t<span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_tag_section\">V </span><span id=\"S5.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_smallcaps\">Conclusion</span>\n1027\t</h2>\n1028\t\n1029\t<div id=\"S5.p1\" class=\"ltx_para\">\n1030\t<p id=\"S5.p1.1\" class=\"ltx_p\">We presented CF-Net, a deep multimodal network for the\n1031\tABAW 11<sup id=\"S5.p1.1.1\" class=\"ltx_sup\">th</sup> Ambivalence/Hesitancy challenge.\n1032\tRecognising ambivalence and hesitancy from video is fundamentally\n1033\tdifferent from prototypical emotion recognition: modalities are\n1034\tfrequently incongruent, the validation set is small (124 clips),\n1035\tand the speaker-disjoint splits penalise any system that memorises\n1036\tvisual or acoustic speaker identity.\n1037\tCF-Net addresses these pressures by encoding visual, audio, and\n1038\ttranscript streams with frozen pre-trained backbones and fusing them\n1039\tvia ConflictFusion, which explicitly represents cross-modal disagreement\n1040\tthrough pairwise absolute-difference terms.\n1041\tTraining regularisation — certainty-weighted focal loss, manifold mixup,\n1042\tmodality dropout, and an auxiliary certainty-regression head — prevents\n1043\toverfitting on the small training set.</p>\n1044\t</div>\n1045\t<div id=\"S5.p2\" class=\"ltx_para\">\n1046\t<p id=\"S5.p2.1\" class=\"ltx_p\">The ablation study confirms the value of each component: replacing\n1047\tConflictFusion with simple mean fusion drops Macro F1 by 1.8 pp;\n1048\tthe auxiliary certainty head, focal loss, manifold mixup, and modality\n1049\tdropout together contribute a further 3.7 pp.\n1050\tPer-speaker feature normalisation, switching to a BiGRU temporal encoder,\n1051\tand adopting certainty-weighted focal loss contribute an additional 1.7 pp\n1052\tcumulatively, lifting CF-Net from 0.6984 to <span id=\"S5.p2.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_bold\">0.7155</span> on the\n1053\tvalidation set.\n1054\tOn the private challenge test set, CF-Net achieves <span id=\"S5.p2.1.2\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_bold\">0.7364</span>\n1055\tMacro F1 (AP = 0.7392), a <math id=\"S5.p2.1.m1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"+\" display=\"inline\" intent=\":literal\"><semantics><mo>+</mo><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">+</annotation></semantics></math>0.021 improvement over the validation\n1056\tresult and better than the best published test score\n1057\t(0.714, Team LEYA <cite class=\"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite\">[<a href=\"#bib.bib10\" title=\"Team leya in 10th abaw competition: multimodal ambivalence/hesitancy recognition approach\" class=\"ltx_ref\">14</a>]</cite>), while keeping all backbone\n1058\tweights frozen and training in under 15 minutes on a single consumer GPU.</p>\n1059\t</div>\n1060\t<div id=\"S5.p3\" class=\"ltx_para\">\n1061\t<p id=\"S5.p3.1\" class=\"ltx_p\">Several directions remain open.\n1062\tSelective fine-tuning of the top layers of SigLIP2 or HuBERT\n1063\tunder stronger regularisation could improve modality-specific\n1064\tfeature quality without inducing speaker-identity memorisation.\n1065\tReplacing the fixed ConflictFusion concatenation with a learned\n1066\tcross-modal attention layer <cite class=\"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite\">[<a href=\"#bib.bib24\" title=\"Multimodal transformer for unaligned multimodal language sequences\" class=\"ltx_ref\">20</a>]</cite> may better weight\n1067\twhich modality pairs are in conflict for each sample.\n1068\tDomain-adversarial training on the acoustic stream could further\n1069\timprove robustness to the zero-speaker-overlap constraint of the\n1070\tBAH dataset.</p>\n1071\t</div>\n1072\t</section>\n1073\t<section id=\"bib\" class=\"ltx_bibliography\">\n1074\t<h2 class=\"ltx_title ltx_title_bibliography\">References</h2>\n1075\t\n1076\t<ul id=\"bib.L1\" class=\"ltx_biblist\">\n1077\t<li id=\"bib.bib22\" class=\"ltx_bibitem ltx_bib_article\">\n1078\t<span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_bib_key ltx_role_refnum ltx_tag_bibitem\">[1]</span>\n1079\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_author\">T. Baltrušaitis, C. Ahuja, and L. Morency</span><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_year\"> (2018)</span>\n1080\t</span>\n1081\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_title\">Multimodal machine learning: a survey and taxonomy</span>.\n1082\t</span>\n1083\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_journal\">IEEE transactions on pattern analysis and machine intelligence</span> <span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_volume\">41</span> (<span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_number\">2</span>), <span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_pages\"> pp. 423–443</span>.\n1084\t</span>\n1085\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock ltx_bib_cited\">Cited by: <a href=\"#S2.SS2.p1.1\" title=\"II-B Multimodal Fusion with Explicit Conflict ‣ II Related Work ‣ CF-Net: Conflict Fusion with Speaker Normalisation and Certainty Weighting for Ambivalence/Hesitancy Recognition\" class=\"ltx_ref\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag\">§<span class=\"ltx_text\">II-B</span></span></a>.\n1086\t</span>\n1087\t</li>\n1088\t<li id=\"bib.bib7\" class=\"ltx_bibitem ltx_bib_article\">\n1089\t<span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_bib_key ltx_role_refnum ltx_tag_bibitem\">[2]</span>\n1090\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_author\">S. E. Bekhouche, H. Telli, A. Benlamoudi, S. E. Herrouz, A. Taleb-Ahmed, and A. Hadid</span><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_year\"> (2026)</span>\n1091\t</span>\n1092\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_title\">Conflict-aware multimodal fusion for ambivalence and hesitancy recognition</span>.\n1093\t</span>\n1094\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_journal\">arXiv preprint arXiv:2603.15818</span>.\n1095\t</span>\n1096\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock ltx_bib_cited\">Cited by: <a href=\"#S1.I1.i4.p1.1\" title=\"In I Introduction ‣ CF-Net: Conflict Fusion with Speaker Normalisation and Certainty Weighting for Ambivalence/Hesitancy Recognition\" class=\"ltx_ref\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag\">4th item</span></a>,\n1097\t<a href=\"#S1.p3.1\" title